node.title: More than eight million vaccines given in NZ: What you may have missed in today's COVID-19 update
node.description: Here's a breakdown of Sunday's case numbers and data.
node.content: ["There were 55 new COVID-19 cases on Sunday, a slight increase from Saturday's two-month low in numbers.", "Aside from the daily case numbers, you may have missed the details of the Ministry of Health's latest update.", "Here's a breakdown of Sunday's case numbers and data.", "Of Sunday's 55 new cases, 41 are in Auckland, seven in Taranaki, four in Waikato, and three in Bay of Plenty.", "The exact location of Auckland's cases is not reported by the Ministry of Health.", "There are 1928 people isolating at home, including 530 cases.", "Of Waikato's four new cases, three are in Te K\u016biti and one is in Tokoroa.\u00a0", "Three of the cases have been linked to the outbreak and one is under investigation.", "Two people are receiving care at Waikato Hospital.", "There are 63 people isolating at home.", "All three of the Bay of Plenty's new infections are in Tauranga and all are contacts of previous cases.", "Of Taranaki's seven new cases, four are linked to the Eltham cluster and two to the New Plymouth Case. One case will be officially transferred to Auckland's case numbers as they reside there for work purposes but have a permanent Taranaki address.", "There are a further five cases of Omicron that have been detected in international arrivals, bringing New Zealand's total number of cases with the variant to 13. All of these have been found in MIQ.", "Of these five new Omicron cases, four remain in managed isolation and one has recovered and has been released.", "The recovered case arrived from London via Singapore on December 7.\u00a0 This case tested positive on their day 0/1 testing and was closely managed in MIQ, the Ministry of Health says. They were never in the community while infectious.", "As an added precaution, 30 other passengers on their flight are regarded as close contacts. So far, 27 of these passengers have completed day nine tests and returned negative results and testing is underway for the remaining three.", "Northland:", "Auckland metro DHBs:", "Waikato:", "Bay of Plenty:", "Lakes:", "Taranaki:\u00a0", "Whanganui:", "Hawke's Bay:", "Nelson-Marlborough:", "Canterbury:\u00a0", "Vaccines administered to date:", "Vaccines administered on Saturday:", "Total M\u0101ori vaccine rate:", "Total Pasifika vaccine rate:", "Northland:", "Waikato:", "Lakes:", "Bay of Plenty:", "Tair\u0101whiti:", "Taranaki:", "Hawke's Bay:\u00a0", "MidCentral:", "Whanganui:", "Nelson-Marlborough:", "West Coast:", "South Canterbury:", "Remaining DHBs that are more than 90 percent fully vaccinated:", "There are 56 COVID-positive people in hospital. Of these, 26 are in Auckland City, 15 in Middlemore, 10 in North Shore, three in Tauranga, and two in Waikato.", "Six people are in an intensive care or high dependency unit - two each in Auckland City and Middlemore, and one each in North Shore and Waikato.", "The average age of hospitalised patients is 53.", "The vaccination status of current hospitalisations - which includes Northern Region wards only - is:"]
